To convert a decimal number into another base, one approach involves successively dividing by the target base and recording remainders as digits. Here’s how it works using our problem statement ($555_{10}$, converting to base 5):

Step 1: Divide 555 by 5 getting quotient=111 and remainder=0 -> Write '0'.  
Repeat Steps below while Quotient!=0;  
Step 2: Now take new dividend i.e., 111/5 giving us Q=22 R=1 ,so write ‘1’   
Step 3 : New Dividend=(previous Remainder)*base +Current Division Result-> ((PreviousRemainder*Base)+currentQuotient);    
NewDividend=> [(prevR*5)+Q] => [0*5+22]=22 ;Divided again now..    
Again taking current division results-->quotient=4 reminder=2 -->write digit='2';     
Last time repeating same procedure once more...           
Final Time Against Current Dividend~[((22*(5))+4)] /5
